review.reviewText:
We spent 2 nights in this hotel to get over our jet lag before a month long trip in the US. I highly recommend this hotel:
* hotel staff were all bending over backwards to assist us with any queries we had;
*gym facilities were basic but good;
*free airport shuttle is one of the reason we stayed here (made it easy for us to make a day trip into downtown San Francisco via the BART light rail);
*beds and pillows were really comfortable - clean rooms;
*we initially had a freeway facing room (which was a bit too noisy for us) and when we asked if we could swap, it was no problem (we were moved to a lobby facing room); and
*great Mexican food restaurant nearby.

One suggestion for improvement. I think the WIFI should be free at a hotel which is in this price range (or at least offer free WIFI in the lobby area). We got around this by going to the Marriott Starbucks (via the shuttle bus). Otherwise, they slug you $12.95 per day from memory.
